<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014</DATELINE><TITLE>Birds, Pigs, and People: The Rise of Pandemic Flus</TITLE><BODY>In early April 2009, a ten-year-old boy in San Diego County, California, showed up at an outpatient clinic with fever, severe cough, and vomiting. Suspecting flu, the health worker took a routine throat swab and sent it to the county laboratory.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>